    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                <pb facs="nei.j4b.7.27"/>
                <note type="curatorial">27</note>
                <note type="curatorial">Missouri Collection</note>
                
                <fw type="authorial">
                    DAILY 
                    <figure/> 
                    EDITORIAL DEPARTMENT 
                    ST. LOUIS POST-DISPATCH 
                    PUBLISHED BY THE PULITZER PUBLISHING CO. 
                    ST. LOUIS, MO. 
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        Sept. 8, '28.
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>
                        Dear Mama:
                    </salute> 
                    <dateline>Branson, Mo.</dateline>
                </opener>
                
                <p>I'm surely gald the radio has arrived at last! Have the man tell you if it's all there and let me know. I am still trying to get a 25 cycle trickle charger. Montgomery Ward say$ they can't furnish. I'm after Sears Roebuck. But even if you don't get the charger, you can have Binkley charge the big battery when needed.</p> 
                <closer>
                    <salute>Endless love,</salute> 
                    <signed>Jno.</signed>
                </closer> 
                <postscript><p>Find out all you need to know from the man who imitates - about
                    batteries &amp; about turning off the tales when not in use. Watch this particularly.</p></postscript> 
                
            </div1>
            
        </body>
        
